    <h5>Tips</h5>
    <p>The best way to learn is by looking at Zurbs work, especially the marketing site, start by cloning this work which is why they share it on their repository.</p>

    <p>Plan you design ahead, when working with Zurb Foundation is a little different than Sass; Not as many mixings necessary, since layout is controller by markup. Example class="columns six" will take care of position and sizing.</p>

    <p>Follow this sheet sheet of classes so that its easier to code using your favorite templating engine. </p>

